    "encrypted": "false",
    "long_instructions": "##  🔍Teacher Tip\r\n\r\nIn this activity, you'll get a chance to explore co-creating with AI. Specifically, you’ll collaborate with an AI assistant to help plan, write, or revise social media posts for your school’s official social media account.\r\n\r\nIn this level you'll act as the **pilot** while AI will act as the **co-pilot**.\r\n\r\nOn the next level, you'll switch, with AI acting as the **pilot**.\r\n\r\nWhile you're working through these levels, reflect on *where did you find each type of collaboration useful? And which type of AI collaboration did you prefer and why?*\r\n\r\n<p style=\"font-size: 18px; font-weight: bold; background-color: #F5F7F8; padding: 10px; border-left: 5px solid #8148B2; display: inline-block;\">➡️ The following levels are from Lesson 10. You can find more details in the full <a href='https://studio.code.org/s/aif1-2025/lessons/10' target='_blank' rel='noopener noreferrer' style='text-decoration: none; font-weight: bold;'>Lesson Plan</a>.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## You as Pilot. AI as Co-Pilot.\r\n\r\nOn this level:\r\n- **You** will act as the **pilot**, making all the updates to the social media post yourself.\r\n- **AI Chat** will act as a **co-pilot**, giving you suggestions to improve your social media post.\r\n\r\n### Do This:\r\n\r\n1. Write a short **social media post** for your school’s official social media account. It may be about promoting a social event, celebrating or recognizing a student or group of students, or about an educational/outreach campaign.   \r\n2. Input the **social media post** into AI Chat.\r\n3. **Pick which area you want AI give you suggestions** on how to improve your post.\r\n    * Clarity – Is it easy to understand?\r\n\t* Engagement – Does it capture interest?\r\n\t* Originality – Does it feel unique?\"\r\n   \r\n_Note: **DO NOT ask AI to revise** the content for you—only ask for **ideas and suggestions**._\r\n4. **Revise your original post** based on the feedback and any suggestions you want to implement from the AI.\r\n    - *Note: it is fine if you don’t want to implement any of AI’s suggestions.*\r\n\r\n**Try it out!**\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n::: details [**Struggling with creating your post?**]\r\nHere are some examples of what your social media post might look like:\r\n- **Event Promotion**\r\n    - _Example: 🎭 Don’t miss our spring play “The Curious Incident of the Dog in the Night-Time” this Friday at 7PM in the auditorium. Tickets on sale now! #SchoolTheater #SupportTheArts_\r\n- **Celebrations and Recognitions**\r\n    - _Example: 👏 Huge congrats to Maya R. for winning 1st place at the district science fair! We’re proud of your hard work and creativity. #StudentSpotlight #ProudSchool_\r\n- **Awareness**\r\n    - _Example: 🧠 Feeling overwhelmed? Our counselors are here for you. Drop by the counseling office or check our wellness resources online. #MentalHealthMatters #YouAreNotAlone_\r\n- **Outreach and Recruitment**\r\n    - *Example: 💬 “The best part of our school is __________.”\r\nFuture students want to know—drop your answer below! 👇 #WhyOurSchool #FutureTigers*\r\n\r\n:::",
